Input: retroid - stretch the firmware's fixed home button pulse

The MCU firmware never reports the home button's real state: it emits
a fixed ~150ms BTN_MODE pulse no matter how long the button is held
(long holds emit a BTN_DPAD_DOWN pulse train instead, and the physical
release is never reported). That makes home unusable as a chord
modifier (Guide+A -> Steam QAM on the back-buttonless Flip 2): the
chord window is the pulse itself.

Report the press edge and defer the release by home_pulse_stretch_ms
(default 400, 0 restores raw firmware behavior), swallowing the
firmware's early release edge. Validated at 400ms against the real
MCU timing via a userspace uinput shim on the RP5 (2026-07-22).

--- a/drivers/input/joystick/retroid.c
+++ b/drivers/input/joystick/retroid.c
@@ -10,6 +10,7 @@
  */
 
